title: Brother, Brother
description: Marcus attempts to date a pair of twins by inventing a twin for himself while TJ is assigned to consult the principal on what computers to buy for the school.

title: Don't Do That Thing You Do
Baby, It's You and You and You
description: Piedmont High is hosting a school dance and TJ's family members each book a date for him, forcing him, Marcus and Mo to coordinate a plan for taking all three girls to the dance without them noticing.

title: Dumbstruck
description: Right after the class is assigned a WWII homework TJ accidentally gets knocked on the head by a wooden board and temporarily loses his intelligence.

title: Trial and Error
description: The school's chemistry teacher Mr Bringleman presents to his class a very difficult test after which his grade book is set on fire and Moe becomes the prime suspect. Meanwhile, the school's drama society is setting up a performance of "Inherit the Wind".

title: Book Smart
description: TJ gets into a long debate with his history teacher while Marcus and Mo sign up to be test dummies in a womens' self-defense class to meet girls.

title: The Dating Game
description: In order to keep Deion off her back, Yvette fakes a relationship with Mo and begins developing actual feelings for him. Meanwhile, Floyd makes Marcus work at his roofing company in order to teach him the value of a college education.

title: Love Letters
description: TJ helps Marcus get closer to a girl by writing love letters for him to send to her. She then also asks TJ to write poetry for her to send back to him, leading to TJ falling for her as well. Meanwhile, Yvette teaches Mo cooking.

title: T.J. versus the Machine
description: TJ's skills in chess gives him the chance to play against a computer, Socrates that's supposed to be unbeatable in chess and Marcus plans to win big on money bets.

title: Men Working Badly
description: The Henderson men try to surprise Yvette by building her a bathroom of her own. Meanwhile, TJ and Mo do an assignment together where they have to pretend to be a married couple.

title: Most Hated Man on Campus
description: TJ tutors the basketball team's inept star player in World History. Unfortunately, he becomes so engrossed in the history of Ghandi that he considers quitting the team.

title: Goodbye, Mr. Chimps
description: TJ tries to educate a monkey for a research center. Meanwhile, Marcus and Mo starts selling the healthy chocolate brand Alfa-Boost 2000 for Deion.

title: Something Wicked This Way Comes
description: While Mo's parents go on the honeymoon they never had, he becomes a house guest at the Henderson's, setting off some arguments between the family members.

title: Love Bug
description: Marcus tries to get everyone out of the house so he can be alone with a girl rumored to be easy, but has to pick up TJ from a sleepover when he gets sick on the big night.

title: That's My Momma
description: When Mo discovers he's adopted, TJ, Marcus and Yvette help him find his real parents.

title: Beating Is Fundamental
description: TJ is accepted into MENSA, where Floyd meets the attractive single mother of another member. Unfortunately, she has an insufferable, arrogant son who makes the rest of the Hendersons' lives hell. Meanwhile, Marcus and Mo open a small hair cutting salon for a school assignment.

title: T.A. or Not T.A.
description: Marcus' attempt to shortcut his way through school hits a road bump when TJ is assigned to be a teacher's assistant in math.

title: Break Up Not to Make Up
Diary of a Mad Schoolgirl
description: While Marcus uses T.J.'s computer to read a girls diary in order to find out what kind of guy she likes, Floyd and Mo start barbecuing together, but their pastime soon gets the better of them.

title: I Was a Teenage Sports Wife
